caption: Friendly staff and a small, comfortable theater with terrific sound and video. The menu prices are quite reasonable and the basket of fries/tots a generous portion for two.

I read about this place on Time Out NY and decided to take my date there to see a movie. Most people were there because they also show movies outside which they call Syndicate sidewalk. On their site they advise people to be there an hour early to be seated for the movie since it’s first come first serve. The movie started at 8 so we got there at 7 sharp. There was already a line that when around the block but that was fine. After an hour everyone that was in line for the move noticed that everyone that was seated from the previous movie wasn’t getting up which didn’t make sense.  I asked someone what was going on and why nobody was being seated after and hour and that the movie we came to see had already started. She said that people didn’t have to get up if they didn’t want to and could just continue watching movies if they pleased and that we’d have to wait and additional 3 hours on top of the hour we already waited. Unfortunately nobody in line ever got seated, or serviced which was a huge disappointment. Please be mindful when choosing the Syndicate for your evening event or at the very least don’t show up for their 8pm showings.
